Shut Up and Sing;;86;;89;;R;;Filmmakers Barbara Kopple and Cecilia Peck examine the consequences of an anti-Bush comment. In 2003 Natalie Maines, singer for the Dixie Chicks, makes a negative comment about President George W. Bush. Controversy follows the group as fans and Republicans show their rage about the remark.;;Documentary;;Barbara Kopple,Cecilia Peck;;2006;;NC;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/dixie_chicks_shut_up_and_sing